  <include>examples/lib_project_example.ts</include>
</lib_project>

Prompt Dependencies:
- lib_project_TypeScript.prompt — provides `loadProject` for base path resolution

Instructions
- Reconstruct file path: `const filePath = path.join(process.cwd(), ...params.path)`.
- Security check: `const resolved = path.resolve(filePath); const allowed = [path.resolve('outputs'), path.resolve('remotion/public')]; if (!allowed.some(d => resolved.startsWith(d))) return 403`.
- Parse Range header: `const range = request.headers.get('range')`. If present, parse `bytes={start}-{end}`.
- Use `fs.statSync(filePath)` for file size; use `fs.createReadStream(filePath, { start, end })` for range reads.
- Convert Node.js `ReadableStream` (from `fs.createReadStream`) to Web API `ReadableStream` using `Readable.toWeb()` or `ReadableStream.from()`.
- `Content-Range: bytes {start}-{end}/{total}` header.
- `Accept-Ranges: bytes` header always present.
- Export `export async function GET(request: Request, { params }: { params: { path: string[] } })`.

Deliverable
- `app/api/video/[...path]/route.ts` — video file streaming handler with range support.

Implementation assumptions (explicit)
- Video files are always MP4; no content-type negotiation needed.
- `fs.createReadStream` with `{ start, end }` provides correct byte ranges.
- `Readable.toWeb()` is available in Node.js 18+.

Please produce production-ready prompt content that will generate the module consistent with the above.
